07/07/2006
ATHENS, Greece -- Iraqi Foreign Minister Hoshyar Mahmud Zebari arrived on Thursday (6 July) for a first official visit to Athens. Greek counterpart Dora Bakoyannis assured him that her country respects Iraq's territorial integrity. She also expressed hope the peace and reconciliation would be re-established there soon. The two ministers agreed on the need to boost economic and trade co-operation, with Bakoyannis reiterating Greece's readiness to support Iraq's reconstruction. (ANA - 06/07/06)
